.TH "cpuidle_enter_s2idle" 9 "cpuidle_enter_s2idle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cpuidle_enter_s2idle \- Enter an idle state suitable for suspend-to-idle.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cpuidle_enter_s2idle
.BI "(struct cpuidle_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct cpuidle_device *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
cpuidle driver for the given CPU.
.IP "dev" 12
cpuidle device for the given CPU.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If there are states with the ->enter_s2idle callback, find the deepest of
them and enter it with frozen tick.
